of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief; filed.

Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins in court with attorney Kristian Kanekoa Lindo.  Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins IN CUSTODY.  Christopher J. Ladwig appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court heard sentencing recommendations.

AS TO COUNT #1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 36 MONTHS, with credit for 51 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS. 
 
The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
The defendant is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
* Comply with the standard rules of probation.
* No contact with the residents at the address of 4514 W. Lloyd Street, Milwaukee, WI.
* Cooperate and participate with a mental health evaluation and follow any recommended treatment.
* Cooperate and participate with an AODA assessment and follow any recommended treatment.
* Cooperate and participate with anger management counseling and any other recommended treatment deemed appropriate by the Probation Depart.
* Maintain absolute sobriety and submit to random urine screens.
* Provide DNA sample and PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* Pay the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

OTHER COURT ORDERS:
* Court sets restitution at ZERO.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins in court with attorney Kristian Kanekoa Lindo.  Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins IN CUSTODY.  Christopher J. Ladwig appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

This matter was originally scheduled for a scheduling conference today, however, the parties have now reached an agreement.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form tendered to the Court.

AS TO COUNT #1:  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY "as charged". Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. 

FILED, Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form and Addendum.

Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins in court with attorney Kristian K. Lindo.  Defendant Emmanuel Dontell Higgins in custody.  Laura Crivello for Christopher J. Ladwig appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Donald, Branch 02.  Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty.  Scheduling conference scheduled for April 4, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Electronic Monitoring and Supervision.  Defendant to be monitored by drug testing.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
